{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0a669d87-6ba4-4d8e-a68d-88203204175b","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Additional checks:**\n- Update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions via `dotnet outdated` or manually in the csproj.\n- Review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for anything affecting your app.\n- Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` to verify everything compiles and passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"809e67ad-5385-44d1-8fce-105fc7d93e87","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"6C2E:3766FA:E3AF8F:10B7281:69FE9362"},"id":"3f8d245e-a6f2-4d38-ac07-e1a0f80a8fbc","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:52:41.797Z","parentId":"10c94b00-8c66-4e4a-8369-f3f8f208371b"}
